Package org.eclipse.mosaic.lib.util.scheduling

Interface EventManager

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    EventScheduler
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ApplicationAmbassador, ChainManager, DefaultEventScheduler, EventInterceptor, MultiThreadedEventScheduler
    public interface EventManager
    The event manager stores events and forces further steps that are required to process the event.

      • newEvent

        default EventBuilder newEvent​(long time,
                              @Nonnull
                              EventProcessor... eventProcessor)
        Creates a new EventBuilder object which must be used to setup an event. Eventually, the EventBuilder.schedule() method must be called to add the event to this EventManager.
        Parameters:
        time - the time the new event should be scheduled
        eventProcessor - the processor to process the event when scheduled
        Returns:
        an EventBuilder instance to create the Event
